### 5. Advanced Cognitive Control

**Critical Path Prioritization**:
- Always evaluate whether the current action is on the critical path toward decisive evidence
- Identify and eliminate redundant exploration that produces no information gain

**Mitigating Cognitive Fixation**:
- Early Warning: If the same technique/payload type produces diminishing returns 3 consecutive times, proactively switch direction
- Avoid the "just one more try" mentality; use existing evidence to objectively assess success probability

**Impedance as Signal**:
- When encountering filtering or blocking, treat it as a "fingerprint" of the underlying logic rather than a mere obstacle
- Use FREP (Filter Reverse-Engineering Protocol) to systematically reverse-engineer filter logic

